			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				here's the key!<BR>
go to lake of ill omen... the level you get this song you use it to solo... kinda boring but effective:<BR>
<BR>
go the the pillars, snare a mob you wanna fight (i found blues and whites are best for this stratigy)<BR>
run away from the mob DO NOT USE ACCELERANDO.<BR>
while you are running you are bellowing.. make sure you run tward the coast also.<BR>
eventually you will hit the coast and the target will be out of range on bellow chances are it will be outta range of bellow the whole run to the coast also... once you get there stop runing and keep bellowing till they are inrange of it... AS SOON AS THEY ARE IN RANGE hit num lock (autorun) and run along the coast bellowing, do not use accelerando that messes you up, also do not snare,  if you just ran strait you could do this for ever but since the lake is a circle eventually the MOB will catch up ta you, this is when you snare again... run and keep hitting bellow till they are out of range, by the tiem they are out of range you stop and snare runs off... keep bellowing till they're in range again and hot autorun... keep going around the lake like this bellowing you should do 12 dammage if you are 23 and more at higher levels... i found a blue takes all the way around till you get to the streem to FV, going the long way, and a white takes the whole way around the lake like this... then you can grab another and do it again LOL no down time you bairly get hit at all!<BR>
if there's any confusion e-mail me maybe i can clear it up<BR>
-Fayin Truesong &lt;Coinfist&gt;--
