				If this song is not in your regular twist, then you need to delete your bard<BR>
character and go back to playing your warrior!  There are two benefits to<BR>
this song, the best one of which has not even been mentioned in any of the <BR>
previous posts here: 1) it reduces the amount of damage the mob delivers!<BR>
Chained mobs that normally deliver 50 points of damage go down to like 10.<BR>
2) It works JUST like the druid Snare spell: it slows the mob's movement. <BR>
That is &quot;movement&quot;, not attack speed. It will slow a running mob to a walk<BR>
and a severely wounded mob to a dead stop.  Great to stop runners that like to<BR>
run off and gather their friends into deadly trains.<BR>
<BR>
The resistance factor is the same as with any other attack. If the mob is higher<BR>
in level than you, expect frequent resistance, not only to this song but to ALL<BR>
your songs and your melee attacks too! Bard songs are magic. If the mob has<BR>
high MR, ALL your songs will be resisted more.<BR>
<BR>
Gonodar Chordmaster<BR>
Bard Extraordinaire
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
