				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				In using this song a lot, while doing Picklaws in High Keep, it gets resisted a lot BEFORE the critter hits 50% health. After that the song begins to take hold more and more. When the critter gets even lower, it takes better hold.<BR>
<BR>
Would like to get this verified by other users. It is a Singing song, and I think that I am top'd in the skill level, or a point away or so, since I use this thing so much ...<BR>
<BR>
All in all, it is nice and enjoyable. The critter seems to immediately try to hit you to get a stun or a bash in, so the song will stop. Be aware of that. Care should be taken that it is not over riding another snare or root spell being thrown. Let both casters and healers know, so they do not waste mana, and allow you to use this song AFTER the critter is under 50% health, since it costs no mana and it works. <BR>
<BR>
Moshkiae
