			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Yes that is called the Fear,Chains,Bellow combo which is currently known the best way for Bards to kite (get that brass skill up!).<BR>
<BR>
I'm here to also dispell the myth that this song slows the enemy attacks.  That song is L 19 Binding.  THIS song ONLY slows mob movement.  Not sure or don't believe?  Take the Mistmoore challenge which was made by a fellow Bard.  Goes like this:<BR>
<BR>
Find a pledge or initiate of the same level.  Pull one of them and let them attack you for 15 whole seconds and count EVERY punch, kick and bash(missed or not) while using Chains.  Repeat test with no Chains this time.  You'll see that the number of attacks is nearly the same more or less depending on current lag.<BR>
<BR>
Every Bard song except battle party songs is almost unique in a sense.  Unlike casters, we don't need to buy an upgrade of a song.  Its effect is increased over time.  I ask for a response to this ONLY after you really did the MM challenge.<BR>
<BR>
Cymis Stormsong<BR>
E'ci
